.TH "snd_pcm_hw_param_value" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_param_value" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_param_value \- return @params field @var value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_param_value
.BI "(const struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ","
.BI "int *dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "params" 12
the hw_params instance
.IP "var" 12
parameter to retrieve
.IP "dir" 12
pointer to the direction (-1,0,1) or NULL
.SH "RETURN"
The value for field \fIvar\fP if it's fixed in configuration space
defined by \fIparams\fP. -EINVAL otherwise.
